name: Via Leni 6b
infos: Via Leni was one, if not the first modern route in the E face of Spazzacaldeira. Due to the easy access (15 minutes from cable car) on weekends it draws lots of crowds.   It begins with an uneven slab/face. Crux is a slightly overhanging move at the end of pitch 2.   Descent: 20 Meter rap into a small couloir. walk/scramble down SW-The route is located on the left side of the long E face of Spazzacaldeira.-Almost completely equipped with bolts. Light complementary rack suggested for pitch 3 and 4
